Preheat your oven to 200°C. Bring a large #saucepan{} of water with @salt{1/2%tsp} to the boil for the potatoes. Chop the @potatoes{450%g} into 2cm chunks (no need to peel). Halve, peel and chop the @onion{1}(halved, peeled and chopped into small pieces). Separate the @broccoli{1}(separated into florets) into florets. Peel and grate the @garlic{1%clove}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}). When boiling, add the potatoes to the water and cook until you can easily slip a knife through, ~{15-20%minutes}.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat. When the oil is hot, add the @British beef mince{240%g} and cook until browned, ~{3-4%minutes}. Use a #wooden spoon{} to break it up as it cooks.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw mince.

Drain and discard any excess fat from the mince, then season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}. Next, add the onion to the mince and cook until softened, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Add the garlic, @tomato puree{30%g} and @curry powder mix{1%tbsp} to the mince. Fry until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}, continuously stirring. Then stir in the @beef stock paste{10%g} and @water{150%ml} and bring to the boil. Once boiling, reduce the heat and simmer until the sauce has thickened, ~{4-5%minutes}, stirring occasionally. Season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}, add the @peas{120%g} and remove from the heat.

> IMPORTANT: The mince is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Once the potatoes are cooked, drain in a #colander{} and return to the pan, off the heat. Add a knob of @butter{1%knob} and a splash of @?milk{3%tbsp} (if you have any) and mash with a #potato masher{} until smooth. Season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}.

When the keema is ready, transfer it to an appropriately-sized #ovenproof dish{}. Spoon over the mash and spread it out so that the keema is evenly covered. Pop the pie onto the top shelf of your oven and bake until golden and bubbling, ~{15-20%minutes}. Meanwhile, pop the broccoli onto a #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{}, season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{} then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer. Five mins into the pie cooking time, roast the broccoli on the middle shelf of your oven until tender and crispy, ~{10-15%minutes}.

When everything is ready, divide the keema cottage pie between your plates and serve with the roasted broccoli alongside. Enjoy!